chool unions protect the incompetent and reward them, and fire the good teachers. The fix is easy, fire the administration staff 100% replace them with competent people, and make the teachers responsible for their students success. Eliminate passing kids for just showing up in class occasionally and throw the troublemakers out of school. This will hurt the feelings of some kids and parents, but not as much as having a kid graduate that can't do basic math or read, who's live is destroyed. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="801" language="en" documentId="2394" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Gee Bee" date="Aug 30, 2013 7:42PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="14" thumbsDown="0" origId="2394" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="801"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>